In dotnet/runtime we use the [property item conversion feature](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/msbuild/comparing-properties-and-items?view=vs-2019#conversions-between-strings-and-item-lists): https://github.com/dotnet/runtime/blob/master/src/installer/pkg/projects/Directory.Build.props#L166. When using the new NuGet static graph evaluation mode, that property doesn't get expanded. It works fine when setting `/p:RestoreUseStaticGraphEvaluation=false`.

See the generated projects.assets.json below:

```
{
  "version": 3,
  "targets": {
    ".NETCoreApp,Version=v5.0": {
     ...
    },
    ".NETCoreApp,Version=v5.0/@(RestoreBuildRID)": {
      ...
    },
```

